                     <origDate notBefore="1800" notAfter="1830">Early 19th cent. (?)
 Donation
                        of the Ms. by daǧǧāzmāč Ḫagos and the dating should be considered with
                        caution.</origDate>
                  </origin>
               <provenance>According to Additio 1, the Ms. was donated
                     by Ḫagos whose baptismal name is Za-Manfas Qǝddus. He might be identified with
                     the second son of daǧǧāzmāč Sabāgādis
                     (1770-1831), Ḫagos (d. 1831) whose baptismal name is Dāgǝmāwi Za-Manfas Qǝddus.
                     
 However, the note as well as the Ms. look more recent, so his donation
                     should be considered with caution.
 Other Mss. donated by him are Ms.
                     FBM-002 and AMM-004.</provenance></history>
